<TITLE> Iftekhar talks with Pranab at BIMSTEC meet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 28 (bdnews24.com)Foreign adviser Dr Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury had bilateral talks with his Indian counterpart Pranab Mukherjee on Thursday, at the sidelines of the 10th ministerial meeting of the Bay of Bengal Initiative for Multi Sectoral Technical and Economic Cooperation in New Delhi. The two leaders discussed political and economic issues affecting the two countries, said Iftekhar. "Our discussions covered the entire gamut of bilateral relations including political and economic issues," he told bdnews24.com by telephone from New Delhi. "We also discussed means of rendering BIMSTEC a more effective bridge between SAARC and ASEAN," he said. Both Bangladesh and India wanted to discuss ways and means of activating all bilateral and functional mechanisms through holding regular meetings, he said. The foreign adviser also met Thai foreign minister Tej Bunnag on the sidelines of the ministerial gathering. Iftekhar reached the Indian capital Thursday afternoon to attend the ministerial meeting. He is likely to return home Friday, according to the foreign ministry
